review:
Hard to give an opinion about a such product. I've mixed feeling about this game, but my overall feedback is positive.

What I liked:

1) nice musics, translated in many languages, Steam achievements, saves, leaderboards, difficulty levels. Clearly had some work behind;
2) lot of nonverbal languages from models during playing, with wide smiles and worries depending on cards, this makes Poker Show quite fun to play;
3) overall good taste in everything with elegant models (they stops at underwear, I prefer like this);
4) price/contents ratio is fair;
5) out of context, but it's full of nice guitars in the room (look my avatar, I suppose to like guitars more than girls).

What I disliked:

1) 360 video is blurry and sometime something seems wrong in the stereoscopic image, it's eyestrain and crosses my eyes easily, stereo separation is too high or wrong balanced;
2) I was ok without positional tracking two years ago, but now it's weird;
3) scale is off, everything seems huge and deformed;
4) only pad support;
5) all things I disliked makes Poker Show VR not much different than a virtual theatre experience, this doesn't seems real VR to me.
